# Caching

Next.js 16+ — use in-repo docs (`node_modules/next/dist/docs/`), not web search. Start with `08-caching.md` and `09-revalidating.md`.

**Read:** `'use cache'` + `cacheTag(...)` + `cacheLife(...)`; tags only via segment `cache-tags.ts`.

**Write (Server Action, same user must see fresh UI):** `updateTag(tag)` in the **same** action that mutated — not bare `revalidateTag(tag)`.

| Situation                       | API                                            |
| ------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| Action + immediate UI for actor | `updateTag`                                    |
| Action, staleness OK            | `revalidateTag(tag, "max")`                    |
| Route handler / webhook         | `revalidateTag(tag, "max")` or `{ expire: 0 }` |
| By URL segment                  | `revalidatePath`                               |

Never cache or revalidate session reads. Reference: `set-active-organization-action.ts`.

